text: V20 seems pretty pimpin'
morning

So I have a small story to share that happened last week. 

Wednesday my boss wanted to talk to me. Long story short, he tells me that the company run out of money, I can't be paid on Friday and I have two choices: 1) I leave the company, the company stops the projects and goes bankrupt (since I am the one with the technical knowledge of all the projects). 2) I keep working full time, get paid my "minimum living expenses" each month and have patience until the company receives a fund in 2-3 months from now where I get paid what I am owed.

To that I replied: For (1), if I don't receive any of my salary Friday I will be leaving the company. For (2), there is no way I will be working full-time for less money. 

So instead I suggested that (1) either I don't receive any salary and leave the company (2) or I receive some salary and can work for less money but the percentage that I will be paid less, for that same percentage I will have working hours. So if I work 1 day/week I will be paid 1/5 of my salary.

In the end we agreed on 1 day/week for 1/5 of the salary and I received less than half the salary I was supposed to receive Friday with the rest owed to me. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯
I am sharing this so people know what to expect if they join a startup, it's not all fun and games and there is a lot of risk
